<p>Lets say I need to run <strong>methodA</strong> and methodA will throw a FormatException.</p>  <p>If I write this block:</p>  <pre><code>try {     methodA(); } catch (Exception ex) {     methodB(); } catch (FormatException ex) {     methodC(); } </code></pre>  <p>Will it ever run <strong>methodC</strong>, knowing that FormatException is also an Exception and therefor will go into the catchblock of <strong>methodB</strong>.</p>  <p>Or is it better to write it like this:</p>  <pre><code>try {     methodA(); } catch (Exception ex) {     if(ex is FormatException)     {         methodC();     } else     {         methodB();     } } </code></pre>